com.ibm.team.build.client

Interface ITeamBuildRequestClient

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ITeamBuildBaseClient

    public interface ITeamBuildRequestClient
extends ITeamBuildBaseClient
    The ITeamBuildRequestClient interface provides ability to create, retrieve, and manipulate build requests.
    Since:
    0.5

    • Method Detail

      • requestBuild

        IBuildRequest requestBuild(IBuildDefinitionHandle buildDefinitionHandle,
                           boolean allowDuplicateRequests,
                           org.eclipse.core.runtime.IProgressMonitor progressMonitor)
                    throws TeamRepositoryException,
                           java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Provides the ability to request that a build should occur for a particular build definition. Requests will be granted only for build definitions that have at least one active build engine to support them.

        Calling this method results in a build that uses the default build properties specified in the build definition.

        Parameters:
        buildDefinitionHandle - The build definition to request a build for.
        allowDuplicateRequests - Indicates if a duplicate request can be made if one for the type already exists in the queue.
        progressMonitor - The progress monitor to track progress on or null if progress monitoring is not desired.
        Returns:
        • The new build request for the specified build definition.
        • The existing build request if one already exists for the build definition and allowDuplicateRequests is false.
        • null if the request could not be honored.
        Throws:
        TeamRepositoryException - If error occurs when requesting the build.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the buildDefinition or any of the slots in buildProperties are null.

      • requestBuild

        IBuildRequest requestBuild(IBuildDefinitionHandle buildDefinitionHandle,
                           IBuildProperty[] buildProperties,
                           boolean allowDuplicateRequests,
                           org.eclipse.core.runtime.IProgressMonitor progressMonitor)
                    throws TeamRepositoryException,
                           java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Provides the ability to request that a build should occur for a particular build definition. Requests will be granted only for build definitions that have at least one active build engine to support them.

        This method allows the user to specify a list of additional or modified build properties that will override properties included in the build definition.

        Parameters:
        buildDefinitionHandle - The build definition to request a build for.
        buildProperties - Any new or overridden build properties that should be added or replaced as part of the request. This parameter can be null if the default build properties associated with the build definition should be used.
        allowDuplicateRequests - Indicates if a duplicate request can be made if one for the type already exists in the queue.
        progressMonitor - The progress monitor to track progress on or null if progress monitoring is not desired.
        Returns:
        • The new build request for the specified build definition.
        • The existing build request if one already exists for the build definition and allowDuplicateRequests is true.
        • null if the request could not be honored.
        Throws:
        TeamRepositoryException - If error occurs when requesting the build.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the buildDefinition or any of the slots in buildProperties are null.

      • requestBuild

        IBuildRequest requestBuild(IBuildDefinitionHandle buildDefinitionHandle,
                           IBuildProperty[] newOrModifiedBuildProperties,
                           IBuildProperty[] deletedBuildProperties,
                           boolean allowDuplicateRequests,
                           org.eclipse.core.runtime.IProgressMonitor progressMonitor)
                    throws TeamRepositoryException,
                           java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Provides the ability to request that a build should occur for a particular build definition. Requests will be granted only for build definitions that have at least one active build engine to support them.

        This method allows the user to specify build properties that should be deleted from the requested build as well as new or modified properties. Should a property be present in both lists, the deletion list will take priority and the build property will be deleted.

        Parameters:
        buildDefinitionHandle - The build definition to request a build for.
        newOrModifiedBuildProperties - Any new or overridden build properties that should be added or replaced as part of the request. This parameter may be null if no build properties should be added or modified.
        deletedBuildProperties - Any build propertied that should be deleted as part of the request. This parameter may be null if no build properties should be deleted.
        allowDuplicateRequests - Indicates if a duplicate request can be made if one for the type already exists in the queue.
        progressMonitor - The progress monitor to track progress on or null if progress monitoring is not desired.
        Returns:
        • The new build request for the specified build definition.
        • The existing build request if one already exists for the build definition and allowDuplicateRequests is true.
        • null if the request could not be honored.
        Throws:
        TeamRepositoryException - If error occurs when requesting the build.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the buildDefinition or any of the slots in buildProperties are null.

      • requestAndStartBuild

        IBuildRequest requestAndStartBuild(IBuildDefinitionHandle buildDefinitionHandle,
                                   IBuildEngineHandle buildEngineHandle,
                                   org.eclipse.core.runtime.IProgressMonitor progressMonitor)
                            throws TeamRepositoryException,
                                   TeamBuildException,
                                   java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Requests a build by creating a build request for the specified build definition and automatically setting the request into a processed and in progress state specifying the supplied engine as the handling process. No other potential handlers will be given a chance to process the request.
        Parameters:
        buildDefinitionHandle - The build definition to request a build to start for.
        buildEngineHandle - The engine used to process the build.
        progressMonitor - The progress monitor to track progress on or null if progress monitoring is not desired.
        Returns:
        The build request that was used to start the build.
        Throws:
        TeamRepositoryException - If an error occurs when retrieving the pending requests.
        TeamBuildException - If a repository error occurs requesting and processing the build.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the buildDefinitionHandle or buildEngineHandle is null.

                                   java.lang.String[] properties,
                                   org.eclipse.core.runtime.IProgressMonitor progressMonitor)
                            throws TeamRepositoryException,
                                   TeamBuildStateException,
                                   java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Cancels a build request that is pending.
        Parameters:
        buildRequestHandle - The request to cancel.
        properties - The properties to fetch in the build request that is canceled.
        progressMonitor - The progress monitor to track progress on or null if progress monitoring is not desired.
        Returns:
        The request that was cancelled or null if it doesn't exist or is not pending.
        Throws:
        TeamRepositoryException - If error occurs when cancelling the request.
        TeamBuildStateException - If an attempt is made cancel a pending build that is in any state other than "Not Started".
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the IBuildRequestHandle is null or any of the slots in properties are null.

                          throws TeamRepositoryException,

      • makeBuildComplete

        IBuildResult makeBuildComplete(IBuildResultHandle buildResultHandle,
                               boolean buildNotNecessary,
                               java.lang.String[] properties,
                               org.eclipse.core.runtime.IProgressMonitor progressMonitor)
                        throws TeamRepositoryException,
                               TeamBuildStateException,
                               java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Marks the specified build result as a completed build unless buildNotNessary is true. The buildNotNessary parameter provides the ability to allow a build to be requested but then be completed as not necessary if it is later determine that the build did not need to occur(for example, source control was checked and no changes were found so the build doesn't occur).
        Parameters:
        buildResultHandle - The build result to make complete.
        buildNotNecessary - Indicates that a build that was requested was determined not to be necessary.
        properties - The properties to fetch in the build result that is made complete.
        progressMonitor - The progress monitor to track progress on or null if progress monitoring is not desired.
        Returns:
        The build result made complete or null if the build was made not necessary.
        Throws:
        TeamRepositoryException - If an exception occurs making the build complete.
        TeamBuildStateException - If an attempt is made to complete a build as not necessary when it's in a state other than "Not Started" or complete a necessary build in any state other than "In Progress".
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the buildResultHandle is null or any of the slots in properties are null.

      • makeBuildCompleteWithStatus

        IBuildResult makeBuildCompleteWithStatus(IBuildResultHandle buildResultHandle,
                                         BuildStatus buildStatus,
                                         java.lang.String[] properties,
                                         org.eclipse.core.runtime.IProgressMonitor progressMonitor)
                                  throws TeamRepositoryException,
                                         TeamBuildStateException,
                                         java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Mark the build as complete with the status provided as long as the status is more severe than the build result's current status. If the status is a warning and the build was set to ignore warnings, then the status will not be updated.
        Parameters:
        buildResultHandle - The build result to make complete
        buildStatus - The status set on the build result providing it is more severe than the current status of the build. If its the warning status, for it to have an effect the build must be configured to not ignore warnings.
        properties - The properties to fetch in the build result that is made complete.
        progressMonitor - The progress monitor to track progress on or null if progress monitoring is not desired.
        Returns:
        The build result made complete.
        Throws:
        TeamRepositoryException - If an exception occurs making the build complete.
        TeamBuildStateException - If an attempt is made to complete a build as not necessary when it's in a state other than "Not Started" or complete a necessary build in any state other than "In Progress".
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the buildResultHandle is null or any of the slots in properties are null.
        Since:
        0.10.0.1 (RTC 5.0.1)

      • startBuild

        IBuildResult startBuild(IBuildRequestHandle buildRequestHandle,
                        java.lang.String[] properties,
                        org.eclipse.core.runtime.IProgressMonitor progressMonitor)
                 throws TeamRepositoryException,
                        TeamBuildStateException,
                        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Starts the build for the specified build request.
        Parameters:
        buildRequestHandle - The build request to start the build for.
        properties - The properties to fetch in the build result that is associated with the build that is started.
        progressMonitor - The progress monitor to track progress on or null if progress monitoring is not desired.
        Returns:
        The build result associated with the started build or null if it was already started.
        Throws:
        TeamRepositoryException - If an error occurs when starting the build.
        TeamBuildStateException - If an attempt is made to start a build using a request that was not returned by either getNextRequest(IBuildEngineHandle, String[], IProgressMonitor) or getNextRequest(String, IBuildEngineHandle, String[], IProgressMonitor) or a request that has already been started.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the buildRequestHandle or any of the slots in properties are null.
